---
title: Thai Salmon Cakes
servings: 4
tags:
  - entres
---

Preheat the #oven{} to 375°F.

Beat @eggs{2} and mix in @salmon{1%can}, @scallions{3}, @thai chilis{2}, @garlic{2%cloves}, @ginger root{1%inch}(grated), @coconut flour{1%tbsp}, @cumin{1%tsp}, @coriander{1%tsp}, @fish sauce{1%tsp}, @salt{0.25%tsp}, and @coconut oil{1%tbsp}.

Make cakes (approximately 2.5 inches in diameter, 0.25 to 0.5 inches thick).

Bake on a greased #cookie sheet{} for ~{12-20%minutes}, until done.
